<br>
There are only two lure characteristics:<br>
<br>
a) Lure()<br>
b) Dragonbreath<br>
<br>
the vs. Summoned and vs. Undead line have<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> neither</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> of those.<br>
<br>
They are all (including vs. Undead) straight up sv. vs. Magic spells.  The advantage of those spells was supposed to be their ratio in exchange for lower max damage, but as they increase in levels that ceases to be true.<br>
<br>
If these spells were Lure, they would own any other spell for soloing the Hole, but the truth is Char is resisted probably 30% less than vs. Summoned line, and has a higher max damage to boot.<br>
<br>
I also have experience using vs. Undead spells as a Necro and Cleric, let me assure you they are very resistable. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <br><font color=#333333>- </font><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower>The Magician's Tower</a><font color=#333333> - </font><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells>Spells</a> <font color=#333333> - </font><a href="http://www.magecompendium.com/">The Mage Compendium</a><font color=#333333> - </font>  <br><br><table border=0 align=center><tr><td align=center><a href="http://login.ezboard.com/BBSSystem.showUserPaymentScreen" target="_blank">Upgrade your account to ezSupporter...</a></td><td><img src="http://www.ezboard.com/image/spacer.gif" width=15 height=1 border=0></td><td align=center><a href="http://login.ezboard.com/BBSSystem.showUserPaymentScreen" target="_blank">...and never see another ad or pop-up again</a></td></tr></table><CENTER><!-- START BOTTOM GAMES AD SCRIPT -->
